Each year the Board of Trustees and the president of the College shall prepare and submit to the county commissioners:
An annual report;
An operating budget;
A capital budget; and
If required, a long-term capital improvement program.

The operating budget shall show:
All revenues estimated for the next fiscal year classified by funds and sources of income for each campus;
All expenditures requested, including the major functions listed under § 16-304(b) of this title and specification for the direct expenditures for each campus by major function established by the Commission;
All indirect expenditures for institutional support;
All other indirect expenditures; and
Any other information or supporting data required by the county commissioners.
